S&P Says Hong Kong’s Yuan Stocks Eligible for Standard Indexes

-- B y   S h a n i   R a j a
-- 
2011-06-06T22:17:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/s-p-says-hong-kong-s-yuan-stocks-eligible-for-standard-indexes.html
Yuan-denominated Chinese stocks
listed in  Hong Kong  will be eligible for inclusion in all
Standard & Poor’s standard equity indexes, according to a
statement from S&P Indices.  “Any new inclusions of yuan-denominated stocks will be
announced with a minimum of five-day notice via the corporate
action file and/or announcement as required by the specific
impacted indices,” the statement dated yesterday said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shani Raja in Sydney at   sraja4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 